div.p:
What merry Gale shall wée then wish for? vnles it bée to Ferry ouer the Hellespont, and to crosse from Sestus to Abidus, that is to say, from London to the Beare Garden? The company of the Beares hold together still;
                  The Beares are hardly put downe.
                they play their Tragi-Comaedies as liuely as euer they did: The pide Bul héere kéepes a tossing and a roaring, when the Red Bull dares not stir. Into this Ile of Dogs did I therefore transport my selfe, after I had made tryall of all other pastimes.
